sentences: Jeremy Phillip Felton (born July 17, 1987), known professionally as Jeremih ( JERR-əm-eye), is an American singer, songwriter, and record producer.
In 2009, he signed a record deal with Def Jam Recordings.

Jeremih's commercial debut single, "Birthday Sex", peaked at number four on the US Billboard Hot 100 chart—leading his self-titled debut album released in June that year, reaching number six on the US Billboard 200 chart.

The song became the lead single for his third studio album, Late Nights released in December 2015.

He transferred to Columbia College Chicago in 2007 to pursue a degree in music business.
